    "'Top-1 performance': when considering only the first radiologist-provided diagnoses, diagnostic accuracy improved slightly from 154/240 (64.2%, unassisted) to 163/240 studies (67.9%, AI-assisted) read correctly.",
    "Once again, the most pronounced improvements were found among radiologists with less experience (Fig. 2), which aligns with our hypothesized benefit of AI assistance for those radiologists.",
    "Supplementary Tables 2 and 3 detail the counts of correct and incorrect diagnoses and associated predictors for the 'top-1' performance.",
    "Prompt characteristicsRadiologists used GPT-4 in 77.5% of the studies, generating 309 prompts.",
